<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-12-01T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-12-01T06:00:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.13/12–153: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador at Saigon</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Heath</hi></persName>)
                            <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Saigon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-12-01T19:00:00+08:00">December 1, 1953—7
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>942. Sent Paris 271. <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> told me
                        today that immediately after Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Tam</persName>’s return Paris, a new government would be formed.</p>
                    <pb facs="0924" n="892" xml:id="pg_892"/>
                    <p><persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Tam</persName> would be allowed to exit
                        gracefully since <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> would suggest
                        that he take a rest period, the intimation being that he would be recalled
                        to government at a later period. The new government would be a “temporary”
                        government.</p>
                    <p>This meant, <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> said, that
                            <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Tam</persName> would not be making the trip
                        to the States to which he had been invited by reason of his position as
                        Prime Minister.</p>
                    <p><persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> did not indicate who would head
                        or form the new government.</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_HDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Heath</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>